                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/3998: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Vice Consul at Ceiba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Evans</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-30T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 30, 1926—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s October 29, 7 p.m. Navy Department advises Destroyer <hi
                        rend="italic">Gilmer</hi> sailed from Bluefields at 7 a.m. to-day for La
                    Ceiba. Due arrive November 1st. Repeat to Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
